HEADWORD: Ragtime
<hw>Rag"time`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>a rhythm with a
regular accompaniment in two-four time and a melody characterized by
syncopation, first recognized in many negro melodies; also a style of
American music in this rhythm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

